<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>38009</id>
    <title>Please add application/x-stuffitx mime type for .sitx StuffitX files</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">The default mime types list included in the last apache-2.2 distribution has the application/x-stuffit 
mime type associated with .</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">sit (Allume Systems Stuffit format) files.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">However, the Stuffit program has 
recently moved to a new compression method and to a new extension, .sitx (StuffitX).</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">As allume 
systems itself suggests, to prevent the user's browser showing all the binary to the user instead of 
beginning the download a new mime type should be added to apache's mime types list.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Even if your policy about mime types is restrictive about adding new mime types, please consider 
adding this, as it's a new extension for a file format that is already in your official mime types list.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">For reference, please see:
http://support.allume.com/techsupport/qanda.php?id=619</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">P.S.: sorry for my poor english</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
